<li id="c28">
  <div class="cx" id="cx49895683">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">Walmart...</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1201068/49895683#c28?mode=alone;showrate=1#c28">0+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>...is in a <em>completely</em> different business than Costco.</p>
<p>Costco can be thought of as being in the business of <i>selling memberships</i>! They pull in over $2B a year in membership fees while their net profits are about $1.7B a year - the rest of the business is just to keep people buying memberships (yes, this is an oversimplification because selling/administering membership does have some costs so the fees are not pure profit)! Walmart has no membership income.</p>
<p>Walmart supercenters, on the average, stock 142,000 different items - some of which probably only sell a few a month. Costco, on the other hand, stocks about 3,300 to 3,800 items per warehouse store and most of them have very high turnover.</p>
<p>At Walmart, most individual items are handled at least twice by a store employee (once to put it on the shelf from the case, once at checkout). As well, due to the selection of products, some of which sell infrequently, a significant percentage of items require "additional" touches by a store employee to "clean up" the shelves on a regular basis. At Costco, many individual items are touched only once by a store employee (at checkout) as cases are put on the "shelves" and customers "uncrate" them into their carts.</p>
<p>As well, the average selling price per item is <i>much</i> higher (due to package sizes and, on the average, higher end merchandise) at Costco than Walmart so even if the same number of "employee touches" were required, the revenue per touch would be <i>much</i> higher than at Costco.</p>
<p>Obviously, labor costs are <i>much</i> more important to Walmart's bottom line and product pricing than Costco.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  <p class="sig"></p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:48607">WillR</a> on <a href="/comments/1201068/49895683#c28">Sat Apr 13, 2013 at 03:21:41 PM PDT</a></p>
  <p class="cl">
  
 
 
  [ <a href="#c15">Parent</a> ] 
    
   

 
 
 </p> 
  </div>
  </div>
</li> 


	


	<ul id="k49895683" class="cm i1">




<li id="c30">
  <div class="cx" id="cx49896011">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">WlaMart has no membership income?</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1201068/49896011#c30?mode=alone;showrate=1#c30">1+ / 0-</a>)</span>
