  <div class="ct">
  
<p>They sold off Sam's Club?</p>
<p>I don't hear the WalMart CEO or the Sam's Club management advocating for an increased minimum wage, despite Sam's Club having the identical business model. I've never heard that Sam's Club employees are well-treated; I have heard that about Costco employees.</p>
<p>And Costco has 174,000 employees - a $1 increase in the minimum wage, even if most of those employees don't work a 40 hr week on average, is still a serious chunk of cash. Yet they're in favor of an increase.</p>
<p>I still don't see why I shouldn't support companies with business models that include treating employees well. And I haven't been in a WalMart or Sam's in over 20 years.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  <p class="sig">
No matter how cynical you become, it's never enough to keep up - Lily Tomlin
</p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:6841">badger</a> on <a href="/comments/1201068/49896011#c30">Sat Apr 13, 2013 at 04:00:19 PM PDT</a></p>
