  <a href="/user/uid:219706">judyms9</a>, <a href="/user/uid:330318">JerryNA</a>, <a href="/user/uid:332723">LaraJones</a>, <a href="/user/uid:306236">musiclady</a>, <a href="/user/uid:222556">fenway49</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>Democrats running NYC, LA, San Francisco, Boston, Chicago, and other high cost of living cities are not doing their job in regards to a minimum wage.</p>
<p>Reasonable minimum wage laws will not exist until the minimum wage reflect the local cost of living. &nbsp;</p>
<p>The cost of living in the US varies so widely, that no single minimum wage can make economic sense across the country.</p>
<p>The Democrats not supporting the $9 and $10/hr proposals are from places that have low costs of living - as they think the increase would make the minimum too high for the area they represent.</p>
<p><b>A person making &nbsp;the current minimum wage of $7.25/hr in Tulsa, OK would need to make $17.62 in New York City to have the same purchasing power. &nbsp;Meanwhile, the current minimum wage in NYC is only $7.25/hr - the Federal minimum wage.</b></p>
<p>So NYC has a minimum wage equivalent to a min wage of $3/hr in Tulsa and Pres Obama's proposal for $9 is equivalent to $3.70/hr min wage in Tulsa. &nbsp;For all practical purposes, NYC does not have a minimum wage. &nbsp; The cost of living between these two cities are so large that a single minimum wage for these two cities cannot make sense. &nbsp;</p>
<p>Minimum wage laws need to be &nbsp;set at different rates to reflect the local cost of living. &nbsp;<strong>The major failure of minimum wage laws are in the high cost of living cities - which ironically are run mainly by Democrats at the local and State level (NYC, LA, San Francisco, Chicago, Washington DC, Boston, etc.) and none have local min wages that come anywhere near a cost of living adjusted $7.25/hr which would be $14 to $18/hr.</strong></p>
<p>Having the minimum wage vary by location, based on BLS cost of living data for low income households would allow members of the House and Senate from low cost of living locations to support the move, while also having a meaningful minimum wage in high cost of living locations.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  <p class="sig">The most important way to protect the environment is not to have more than one child.</p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:142501">nextstep</a> on <a href="/comments/1201068/49894045#c18">Sat Apr 13, 2013 at 12:02:59 PM PDT</a></p>
