<li id="c20">
  <div class="cx" id="cx49894087">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">regional</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1201068/49894087#c20?mode=alone;showrate=1#c20">2+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:142501">nextstep</a>, <a href="/user/uid:330318">JerryNA</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>What I would like to see is a regional minimum wage . &nbsp;For instance a fari wage for unskilled work in texas is somewhere between $11-14 an hour. &nbsp;That should be minimum wage. &nbsp;However, other states have a much higher cost of living. &nbsp;A fair wage in Washington state, for instance, might be closer to $15-20 an hour. &nbsp;I think that this compromise would significantly reduce the debate in the minimum wage because places where it does not cost so much to live will not have to overpay when they can't really sell their product at higher prices.</p>
<p>For instance, lets say that we were able to make the minimum wage a base of $10 an hour, then encourage every state and local through federal pressure to adjust for cost of living. &nbsp;Bad conservative places like Texas won't oppose too much because they will be able to argue that cost of living adjustment will only require about $9 an hour, while Seattle will have the backing to mandate a progressive $15 an hour.</p>
<p>Because when we count apples, the minimum wage is not about the cost increase that it might incur at unskilled jobs, it is the cost to acquire skilled labor. &nbsp;Right now, one can acquire a college graduate to do semi-skilled work for about twice of minimum wage. &nbsp;If minimum wage were to increase from $7 to $10, then one might expect to have to pay $20 for a college graduate, which would be a significant increase. &nbsp;</p>
<p>But like guns now, I think the left really got hoodwinked on wages over the past 15 years of so. With all the free money and low wages for the middle class, and all the military jobs anyone, even the unfit, could fill, no one notice that there were no real paid jobs.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  <p class="sig"></p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:237660">lowt</a> on <a href="/comments/1201068/49894087#c20">Sat Apr 13, 2013 at 12:07:40 PM PDT</a></p>
  <p class="cl">
  
 
 
  
    
   

 
 
 </p> 
  </div>
  </div>
</li> 


	





