  <div class="ct">
  
<p>While the Representative from Minnesota is trying to see what it is like trying to survive on the minimum wage, what we really need to do is pull a "Trading Places" moment on these bureaucrats in office.</p>
<p>Call it Survivor in the "real world" if it makes it clearer to you.</p>
<p>- Take the Representative into a room...<br />
- Have him remove all his clothes and belongings on the table.<br />
- Hand him some worn out clothes that haven't been washed in months to wear.<br />
- Blindfold him and drop him off in the backwoods of Mississippi or some other depressed area without any identification.</p>
<p>Don't tell him when you <strong>might</strong> be back for him. Just drop him off and leave him to rot on his own for a good looooonnnggg time. No cameras. No press. Just himself. No money or credit. Not even his name to rely on. Then let's see how he feels in a few months. Hmmm?</p>

  </div>
